DETECTOR   (GELI) For gamma detection
           (SCIN) Scintillation layer counter for beta detection
PART-DET   (DG)   Decay gamma of 237U and 24Na
           (B-)   Beta-minus of 24Na
SAMPLE      Np-oxide placed in thin-walled containers of 10 mm
           diameter, 2-3 mm height. Samples weight 140-400 mg.
           Np was prepurified from Pu isotopes by a factor of
           about 10**5. Background of Pu-236 was within 0.1% of
           the induced one.
METHOD     (ACTIV,CHSEP) Each sample was irradiated for 80-100 hr.
           Np-236 decays to Pu-236 by beta(-) emission.
           Cross section for Np-237(n,2n)Np-236 reaction was
           measured by detection of alpha particle emission
           from Pu-236.
           After irradiation,Pu-236 was radiochemically separated.
           For this purpose, Pu-239 was used as tracer and
           the cross section was calculated by formula
            sigma(n,2n)=A*(n(Pu-236)/n(Pu-239))*(1/(N*f*l*W))
            where
           A- Pu-239 activity
           n(Pu-236)/n(Pu-239) - ratio of alpha intensities from
                                Pu-236 and Pu-239
           N- number of Np-237 nuclei in the sample
           f- neutron flux
           l- decay constant for Pu-236
           W- beta(-) decay probability for Np-236 = 0.48+-0.01
CORRECTION   Correction on neutron flux fluctuations < 10% .
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) uncertainty includes:
           (ERR-1,,4.) Flux determination
           (ERR-2) Uncertainty in the number of Np-237 nuclei
           (ERR-3) Uncertainty of Pu-239 activity
           (ERR-4,,3.) Uncertainty in the ratio of alpha-particles
                 from Pu-236 and Pu-239
           (ERR-5) Error of beta(-) branching ratio
